# Client App — API Layer (Post-Migration)

## API client — single source of truth

All HTTP calls go through `services/apiClient.ts`. Never use `fetch` or `axios` directly in hooks or components.

```typescript
// services/apiClient.ts
import auth from '@react-native-firebase/auth';

const BASE_URL = process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL ?? 'http://localhost:3000';

async function getAuthHeader(): Promise<Record<string, string>> {
  const token = await auth().currentUser?.getIdToken();
  if (!token) throw new Error('Not authenticated');
  return { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` };
}

export const apiClient = {
  async get<T>(path: string): Promise<T> {
    const res = await fetch(`${BASE_URL}${path}`, {
      headers: await getAuthHeader(),
    });
    if (!res.ok) throw new ApiError(res.status, await res.json());
    return res.json();
  },
  async post<T>(path: string, body: unknown): Promise<T> { /* same pattern */ },
  async patch<T>(path: string, body: unknown): Promise<T> { /* same pattern */ },
};
```

## No more `httpsCallable` — ever

Every Firebase callable must be replaced. Never add new callables. The replacement map:

| Old callable | New REST call |
|---|---|
| `getNearbyDriversForMap` | `GET /drivers/nearby?lat=&lng=&radius=` |
| `getRideHistory` | `GET /rides/history?limit=` |
| `suggestLocation` | `POST /locations/suggest` |
| `retrieveLocation` | `POST /locations/retrieve` |
| `searchLocations` | `POST /locations/search` |
| `getLocationHistory` | `GET /locations/history` |
| `saveLocationToHistory` | `POST /locations/history` |
| `getRouteDirections` | `GET /directions?fromLat=&fromLng=&toLat=&toLng=` |

## WebSocket hook — useRideSocket

After `createRide` succeeds, connect to WS and listen for ride events:

```typescript
// hooks/useRideSocket.ts
export function useRideSocket(rideId: string | null) {
  const [driverLocation, setDriverLocation] = useState<LatLng | null>(null);
  const [rideStatus, setRideStatus] = useState<RideStatus>('pending');

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!rideId) return;
    const ws = connectRideWebSocket(); // authenticate + subscribe

    ws.on('ride:accepted', (payload) => setRideStatus('accepted'));
    ws.on('driver:location', ({ lat, lng }) => setDriverLocation({ lat, lng }));
    ws.on('ride:completed', () => setRideStatus('completed'));

    return () => ws.close();
  }, [rideId]);

  return { driverLocation, rideStatus };
}
```

## React Query — query key conventions

```typescript
export const queryKeys = {
  drivers: {
    nearby: (lat: number, lng: number) => ['drivers', 'nearby', lat, lng] as const,
  },
  rides: {
    history: (limit: number) => ['rides', 'history', limit] as const,
  },
  locations: {
    history: () => ['locations', 'history'] as const,
    suggest: (query: string, sessionToken: string) => ['locations', 'suggest', query, sessionToken] as const,
  },
  directions: {
    route: (from: LatLng, to: LatLng) => ['directions', from, to] as const,
  },
};
```

## Demo mode

Demo mode (`EXPO_PUBLIC_USE_DEMO=true`) must still work post-migration:
- `driversService`: return mock drivers when `getNearbyDrivers` returns empty
- `useRideSocket`: mock events in `__DEV__` if no server available
- Test auth: `+221775551234` / OTP `123456`

## Token refresh

Firebase tokens expire after 1h. The API client must handle 401 responses:
```typescript
// On 401 → force token refresh → retry once
if (res.status === 401) {
  await auth().currentUser?.getIdToken(true); // forceRefresh=true
  return fetch(/* retry */);
}
```
